The paper proposes a method for reducing the size of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) while maintaining their performance. This is a common problem in computer vision (CV) research, which suggests that cs.CV is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves machine learning (ML) techniques, which are covered in cs.LG and cs.AI. The proposed algorithm involves analyzing the information flow in the network, which is related to neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper involves natural language processing (NLP) experiments, which are covered in cs.CL.
